"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-06-parisolympics-jevaughn-powell-comes-short-mens-400m\", \"text\": \"KINGSTON, Jamaica- Jamaica's only hope of qualifying for the men's 400m final at the Olympic Games, JeVaughn Powell came up short after he finished fourth in his semi-final heat at Stade de France in Paris on Tuesday.  Powell, who had a long season after competing in the American NCAA season, ran 44.91 seconds behind an impressive run from Great Britain's Matthew Hudson-Smith, the World Championships silver medallist.  Michael Norman of the USA was second in 44.26 seconds and Nigeria's Samuel Ogazi who ran a lifetime best 44.41 seconds to take one of the spots in the final.  Grenada's Kirani James, who is seeking a fourth Olympic medal, led the qualifying with 43.78 seconds.  -Paul A Reid  Tags:  HOUSE RULES\"}"